Key Match Events: Jamal Musiala scored once and set up three more as Germany demolished Hungary 5-0.
Niclas Füllkrug tapped in a Musiala assist in the 27th minute.
Musiala struck on the break in the 58th minute, completing a quick counter-attack.
Florian Wirtz drilled in the third goal after a one-two with Musiala in the 66th minute.
Aleksandar Pavlovic scored his first goal for Germany in the 77th minute.
Kai Havertz converted from the penalty spot in the 81st minute after being brought down by Willi Orban.
Pre-Game Insights: All eyes were on Musiala, Wirtz and Havertz ahead of the match as many expect them to lead a new generation in Germany along with new captain Joshua Kimmich.
Post-Match Reflections: Following the summer's 2024 European Championships on home soil, former captain Ilkay Gündogan and mainstays and World Cup winners Toni Kroos, Thomas Müller and Manuel Neuer retired from international football.
